# WPF UI Rules

- `src/DubliMark.Desktop/Resources/Theme.xaml` is the main design source.
- Do not duplicate styles when an existing resource can be reused.
- Avoid inline styles unless the value is genuinely one-off or computed.
- Controls must be readable: clear labels, stable spacing, visible focus/selection, and no clipped text.
- Remove standard WPF visual noise where it conflicts with the app style.
- Popup and dialog windows must use the shared dark premium look and window chrome patterns.
- Prefer existing app resources such as cards, pills, buttons, combo boxes, and text styles.
- Keep XAML/code-behind changes scoped to UI behavior unless business logic changes are requested.
